  "texts": [
    "The following is immediate from Facts 4.6 and 4.33.1.Fact 4.39 (Principal Possibility Frames, Separativity, and ⊑-tightness).",
    "If P is the set of all principal downsets in ⟨S, ⊑⟩ plus ∅, then the following are equivalent:1.",
    "P ⊆ RO(S, ⊑); 2.",
    "⟨S, ⊑⟩ is separative; 3.",
    "⟨S, ⊑⟩ is ⊑-tight with respect to P.The requirements on principal possibility frames from Facts 4.38 and 4.39 are related as follows.Fact 4.40 (Boolean Lattices)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}